                        <additions>
                            <p>There are a number of marginalia and later additions throughout the
                                manuscript mainly dating from the <date>seventeenth
                                century</date>:</p>
                            <p>On the front cover: <q>N<expan>umer</expan>o 8 <lb/>Jydsk Lowbog.</q>
                            </p>
                            <p>Fol. <locus>1r</locus> (left margin, top): pointing finger</p>
                            <p>Fol. <locus>1r</locus> (bottom margin): <q>A</q>
                            </p>
                            <p>Fol. <locus>3r</locus> (right margin): <q>Item</q> followed by
                                writing in Danish</p>
                            <p>Fol. <locus>3r</locus> (bottom margin): writing in Danish</p>
                            <p>Fol. <locus>6v</locus> (bottom margin): writing in Danish</p>
                            <p>Fol. <locus>8r</locus> (bottom margin): <q>B</q>
                            </p>
                            <p>Fol. <locus>11r</locus> (top margin): <q>Den Anden bogs taffle</q>
                            </p>
                            <p>Fol. <locus>15r</locus> (bottom margin): <q>I<expan>tem</expan> andre
                                    (?)</q>
                            </p>
                            <p>Fol. <locus>12v</locus> (left margin, bottom): <q>8</q>
                            </p>
                            <p>Fol. <locus>13r</locus> (bottom margin): illegible letter forms</p>
                            <p>Fol. <locus>16r</locus> (bottom margin): <q>C</q>
                            </p>
                            <p>Fol. <locus>18r</locus> (right margin): <q>sielf</q>
                            </p>
                            <p>Fol. <locus>23v</locus> (bottom half of page): <q>Wij
                                    Christi=<lb/>ann den <lb/>fierde</q>
                            </p>
                            <p>Fol. <locus>24r</locus> (top and right margins): <q>Den som mig
                                        fö<expan>r</expan>er det er gud min Jesus mig skall ey
                                    faller <lb n="right margin"/>
                                </q> text continues in Danish</p>
                            <p>Fol. <locus>31v</locus>: <q>Taffuulenn Offuer denn tridie bog
                                    <lb/>fortenncker mig icke</q> continues in Danish</p>
                            <p>Fol. <locus>39r</locus> (left margin): <q>Olaus Horneer(?)</q>
                            </p>
                            <p>Fol. <locus>43v</locus> (bottom margin): the alphabet has been
                                written out twice in two lines</p>
                            <p>Fol. <locus>44r</locus> (bottom margin): <q>x x x y y</q>
                            </p>
                            <p>Fol. <locus>45v</locus>: <q>th<expan>e</expan>r er</q> continues in
                                Danish, then in Latin, <q>ad grecas calendas <gap reason="illegible"
                                        extent="5 letters"/> ffec<expan>i</expan>t</q>
                            </p>
                            <p>Fol. <locus>45v</locus>: <q>
                                    <gap reason="illegible" extent="4 letters"/>eris qui non <choice>
                                        <sic>anunciat</sic>
                                        <corr>annunciat</corr>
                                    </choice> verbum dei non <lb/>est diu<gap reason="illegible"
                                        extent="1 letter"/>nus panis quo vesceris</q>
                            </p>
                            <p>Fol. <locus>45v</locus>: <q>Enn domere skall vere Retferdig <add
                                        place="supralinear" hand="scribe">oc snild.</add>
                                    <lb/>Oc aldtidt døme wden vildt :~ <lb/>Handt schall icke tage
                                    for Retten gaffue <lb/>Thi Budt vill dett paa hanom plage :~
                                    <lb/>Som chambyses den wretferdig Domere loedt drenge Oc hans
                                        huu<add place="supralinear" hand="scribe">e</add>dt paa
                                    Domerens stoell henge. <lb/>Der paa hanns Sønn schulde tencke
                                    <lb/>Oc Aldrig loug eller Rett forkrenncke:~</q> (a verse that
                                describes the duties of a judge and relates the story of how <name
                                    type="person">Cambyses</name>, King of <name type="place"
                                    >Egypt</name>, dealt with <name type="person">Sisamnes</name>, a
                                judge who was accused of taking a bribe, by having him flayed and
                                his skin hung behind the judge's chair, and appointing the son of
                                    <name type="person">Sisamnes</name> as his successor.)</p>
                            <p>Fol. <locus>39r</locus> (left margin): <q>Olaus Horneer(?)</q>
                            </p>
                            <p>Fol. <locus>45v</locus> (bottom margin): <q xml:lang="da">Söfren
                                    Chresten=<lb/>sen aar <lb/>1.6.2.4.</q>
                            </p>
